                            <comment id="15007035" author="junrao" created="Mon, 16 Nov 2015 18:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought the current logic is that if a group is being uploaded, the group is not accessible until the upload completes? Once the upload completes, the group should have the latest info.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15007059" author="hachikuji" created="Mon, 16 Nov 2015 18:27:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=junrao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;junrao&quot;&gt;junrao&lt;/a&gt; That is correct. The problem is that the group may be loaded more than once and the cached metadata object which holds group and member state may be replaced. When this happens, you can get very strange behavior since join/sync response callbacks may be lost and delayed operations (which still refer to the original metadata object) can cause conflicts. My patch makes this safer by preventing this replacement from taking place when a partition is loaded and by cleaning up the group state when the cached metadata is unloaded due to partition emigration to a new leader.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
